ciscoWanCesRsrcPartMIB.name: ciscoWanCesRsrcPartMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of the MIB. The content of this MIB was originally available in CISCO-WAN-AXIPOP-MIB defined using SMIv1. The applicable objects from CISCO-WAN-AXIPOP-MIB are defined using SMIv2 in this MIB. Also the descriptions of some of the objects have been modified.

ciscoWanCesRsrcPartMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-wanatm@cisco.com
ciscoWanCesRsrcPartMIB.description: The mib module to configure the resource partition on Circuit Emulation Service(CES) ports. This is applicable for service modules providing the Circuit Emulation Services.

cesmPortCnfResPartGrpTable.name: cesmPortCnfResPartGrpTable
cesmPortCnfResPartGrpTable.description: This table is for configuring the resource partition parameters.

cesmPortCnfResPartGrpEntry.name: cesmPortCnfResPartGrpEntry
cesmPortCnfResPartGrpEntry.description: An entry for a resource partition. A resource partition have to be created before connections can be added to the logical ports.

cesmResPartPortNum.name: cesmResPartPortNum
cesmResPartPortNum.description: The value of this object identifies the CES port. The value of this object must be same as the value of 'cesPortNum' from cesmPortCnfGrpTable.

cesmResPartCtrlrNum.name: cesmResPartCtrlrNum
cesmResPartCtrlrNum.description: This object identifies the controller which can be used for accessing the resources. The possible values are : par(1) : Portable Auto Route controller. : This value is applicable in Release 1.x. pnni(2): PNNI Controller. : This value is applicable in Release 2.x. tag(3) : MPLS(Formerly known as Tag Switch)Controller

cesmResPartRowStatus.name: cesmResPartRowStatus
cesmResPartRowStatus.description: This object is used for adding/deleting/modifying resource partition on a CES port. In MGX Release 1.x: To add an entry, this object should be set to add(1), value for other objects should not be specified. In MGX Release 2.x: To add an entry, this object should be set to add(1). To delete an entry, this object has to be set to del(2). The resource partition can be deleted only after deleting all the connections (LCNs).

cesmResPartNumOfLcnAvail.name: cesmResPartNumOfLcnAvail
cesmResPartNumOfLcnAvail.description: This represents number of LCNs available for this controller and this port. In CESM-T3/E3 and 8-T1/E1,this value is 1.

cesmResPartLcnLow.name: cesmResPartLcnLow
cesmResPartLcnLow.description: This represents low end of reserved LCN In CESM-8T1/E1 and T3/E3, this refers to the logical port.

cesmResPartLcnHigh.name: cesmResPartLcnHigh
cesmResPartLcnHigh.description: This represents high end of reserved LCN In CESM-8T1/E1 and T3/E3, this refers to the logical port.

cesmResPartIngrPctBW.name: cesmResPartIngrPctBW
cesmResPartIngrPctBW.description: The percentage of total ingress bandwidth reserved. In CESM-8T1/E1 and T3/E3, as there is only one LCN per port and it could be used by only one controller,this value is 100% for that controller.

cesmResPartEgrPctBW.name: cesmResPartEgrPctBW
cesmResPartEgrPctBW.description: The percentage of total egress bandwidth reserved In CESM-8T1/E1 and T3/E3, as there is only one LCN per port and it could be used by only one controller,this value is 100% for that controller.

cesmResPartCtrlrID.name: cesmResPartCtrlrID
cesmResPartCtrlrID.description: This is the controller identifier for the resource patition. The default value is set for PNNI controller.

ciscoWanCesRsrcPartCompliance.name: ciscoWanCesRsrcPartCompliance
ciscoWanCesRsrcPartCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Broad band Interface Resource Partition MIB.

ciscoWanCesRsrcPartGroup.name: ciscoWanCesRsrcPartGroup
ciscoWanCesRsrcPartGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the resource partition configuration on CES ports.
